      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "It is very important that when we do this we have NO EXPECTATIONS! We are totally in assessment mode – discovering what is – how do we feel – how does our horse feel – being honest but not being critical. And staying balanced – things are never all bad or all good! It is useful to give words to what we see/feel. For example, he feels full of excitement today, he feels tight through the shoulders, I feel tight in my right shoulder and neck, etc.",
